Three women in Homa Bay county have expressed their interest in running for election next year, as leaders encouraged them to contest.Woman representative Gladys Wanga said, There is need for women to be at every level of representation. Former Karachuonyo MP Phoebe Asiyo yesterday said women should also run for governor and Senate.Lillian Gogo wants to run for Rangwe MP and Rosemary Rumo will make her third stab at Ndhiwa MP on a Jubilee Party ticket. Judy Kamaria will run for MP but is still consulting whether to contest in her home area Mbita or in Homa Bay town.In Homa Bay county, Millie Odhiambo (Mbita) is the only elected female MP in a post not reserved for women.